{"at": "2026-06-01T15:32:56Z", "commit_ref": "none", "intent": "spec", "actor": "agent", "kind": "output", "content": "Authored .spec-md for spec 0024 from the operator plan specs/0022/.manual/018-ui-wiring-plan.md: wire the tested Avalonia-free Optical Constructor MVU core into a live Avalonia.FuncUI app.\n\nShape: an 8-part arc (U1..U8) ordered by priority, U1 marked CRITICAL — land first. U1 establishes the root Elmish MVU host (new OpticalConstructor.Ui/Shell.fs), rewrites the placeholder AppShell shell to switch on panel id, renders the stack panel read-only, and adds the ui-smoke gate plus a new headless OpticalConstructor.Ui.Tests project. U2 stack editing + async node-solve Cmd; U3 materials panel; U4 sources panel; U5 chart panel + reusable renderer-host adapters (ChartHosts.fs); U6 results/schematic/workspace; U7 synthesis/fit + background jobs; U8 lifecycle (open/save/new/templates/gallery), env persistence, and a 2D-Canvas-first 3D view.\n\nBinding constraints (§0): freeze the tested core; public Avalonia.FuncUI 1.6.0 NuGet only, no clone reference; public-Avalonia DockPanel/Grid/GridSplitter for docking; every off-thread dispatch marshaled via Dispatcher.UIThread.Post; non-serializable handles (CancellationTokenSource, AvaPlot/WebView2, IStorageProvider) outside the model; no new committable file types; two new gates (ui-smoke, ui-tests).\n\nOperator-UX checklist committed once for the shared window (nav switcher + active state, per-node/per-iteration progress, delete-node and accept-fit confirmation gates, MVU update->view refresh with no manual reload, same-row Accept/Revert/Cancel with distinct CTAs, .sidecars dot-folder cross-checked against .gitignore). Noted the web-app hidden-controls treatment (LLM-profile/web-search selects, .specrc.agent dropdown, nav.html) has no analogue in this desktop app.\n\nAll cited <file>:<line> pointers were verified by Read before committing (Spec 037 B-1). Three corrections to the plan recorded in the spec, codebase-wins: (1) MaterialPreview.show* return Plotly.NET.GenericChart (Analytics/Charting.fs:85 Chart.Line) -> WebView2, not ScottPlot/AvaPlot; (2) committable project files are <name>.ocproj.json (ConstructionPage.fs:225), not .ocproj; (3) JobRunner.startBackground takes only run/onDone (JobRunner.fs:127), progress is threaded through the run loop, so RootModel keeps a single fit-state source of truth (SynthesisFitPage.Model) rather than a duplicate JobModel field.\n\nClosing sections present: Acceptance criteria (AC-U1.1..AC-U8.4), Files in scope (new view modules + edits to AppShell/Program/both fsproj + slnx + two gate files), Test artifacts, References.\n"}
