...\n[tool Bash] {\"command\": \"cd C:/GitHub/Berreman/specs/0024; tail -n 1 .history\", \"description\": \"Verify history decision line appended\"}\nThe history line landed. Now I'll remove the transient content file so the spec folder only carries the in-scope changes:\n[tool Bash] {\"command\": \"cd C:/GitHub/Berreman/specs/0024; rm -f .artifacts/gates-0024-history-content.txt && echo \\\"removed temp content file\\\"; echo \\\"=== bundle gates ===\\\"; python -c \\\"...\nGates cycle for spec `0024` complete. Reconciled `.spec-md` against the `.gates/` tree.\n\n## Decisions (7 rows in `.gate-history`)\n\n**Included (5 → `.spec-bundle.gates`):**\n| gate | why |\n|------|-----|\n| `build` | New `*.fs`, two `.fsproj` (Elmish refs) and `Berreman.slnx` edits; §0.7/AC-U1.4 require build-green. |\n| `unit-tests` | Regression guard on the frozen pure solver (§0.1); operator had it checked; default-include. |\n| `constructor-unit-tests` | §0.7 required-green; frozen UI-less projects under `OpticalConstructor/**` must stay green. |\n| `impl-log-structure` | Universal root gate (per `arc-runner.user-md` default set); every slice's impl-log MD is checked. |\n| `state-of-world-structure` | Universal root gate; every slice's SoW MD is checked. |\n\nAll five are `filter: none`, so no `select` lists.\n\n**Proposed-new (2, NOT added to bundle — operator promotes the descriptors):**\n- **`ui-smoke`** → `.proposed-gates/OpticalConstructor/ui-smoke.gates` — headless launch/render gate (§U1.6/§U1.7/AC-U1.3). Command form quoted from §U1.6, runtime baselined on `constructor-unit-tests` (600s). `TODO(agent-uncertain)` on **qualifier** (existing gates only attest `build`/`unit`/`source`).\n- **`ui-tests`** → `.proposed-gates/OpticalConstructor/ui-tests.gates` — headless per-panel view-test gate (§0.7/Test artifacts). `TODO(agent-uncertain)` on **command** (spec pins only the `Category=ui-smoke` trait, so I exclude that subset by negation pending the per-panel trait scheme).\n\nBoth file